ARIYA JUTANUGARN: No.  Actually, when I saw the course I'm like, Oh, this one going to be good for Mo because she really hit solid; she have really great putting.
Obviously she win the tournament, so I guess pretty suit her game.
Q. What about LPGA in Los Angeles?  They've only known for three months.  Great turnout, isn't it?
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: Yeah, great tournament, especially my sister play good this week.  Yeah, it's great one.
Q. Los Angeles, is it a good place for the LPGA?
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: Yeah, of course.  Good course.  Everything is perfect.  I love here.
Q. That's great.  Congratulations to the family.
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: Thanks.
Q. When she dropped her last putt, what you did you say to her?
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: I think I didn't say anything, because I still crying.  So I cry, and then I walk her and hug her.
So I think I didn't say anything yet.
I think I said she cool.
Q. In Thai?
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: In Thai, yeah.
Q. How do you say that?
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: (In Thai.)
Q. You have to be feeling so many emotions right now.  What are you feeling?
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: It's amazing.  I mean, to me, I feel like not only her reach her goal, but I feel like our family reach our goal.  Enough for us.  Right now it's great.
Q. That's so cool.  She was really patient.
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: Yes, she is.  She really, and she inspire me a lot to be patient.
Q. Yeah.  That's so cool.  You have seven wins and then she just watched you and supported you.
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: Uh-huh.
Q. And competed against you.
ARIYA JUTANUGARN: And especially everybody is just going to compare me to her.  What we know is we never compare each other to other.  We just know we going to do our best and try our hardest.  That's all.






